<body>
<!--
  TENANCY MODEL (read before wiring up a real backend):
  This app is single-tenant per session — it represents the authenticated view for
  ONE customer only. It starts empty; every invoice, site and consumption data point
  shown is generated from real documents uploaded and validated in this session.
  - There is no "switch client" or "Add Client" capability anywhere in this app, by design.
    A customer must never be able to see or select another customer's account.
  - The backend must resolve the tenant/account ID from the authenticated session
    (e.g. a server-verified JWT claim), never from anything passed by the browser
    (query param, form field, localStorage, etc.) — every invoice/site/contract/
    validation query must be scoped to that tenant ID server-side.
  - If Unitech staff also need a multi-client "asset manager" view to manage several
    customers' portfolios, that is a DIFFERENT tool with its own auth/role, not a mode
    of this app — mixing the two in one codebase is how cross-tenant data leaks happen.
-->


<div id="auth">
  <div class="auth-left">
    <div class="auth-left-content">
